channel.name: Fox News US
channel.title: The Five
channel.desc: The weekday opinion show is a roundtable ensemble of five rotating Fox News personalities who discuss and debate the top news stories, controversies and issues of the day, from politics to pop culture. Some of the network's featured people who appear include Greg Gutfeld, Dana Perino and Jesse Watters. The hosts conclude each show by selecting a topic of their choice for the "One More Thing" segment.

channel.name: Fox News US
channel.title: Live: FOX and Friends Saturday
channel.desc: Saturday early risers get a chance to experience their own news, information and entertainment that "FOX and Friends" viewers get during the week with this weekend version of the show, currently hosted by Pete Hegseth. In addition to reporting and discussion of the latest news, the show features weather forecasts to help viewers plan their weekend activities.

channel.title: Live: The Journal Editorial Report
channel.desc: Wall Street Journal editor Paul Gigot serves as moderator on this weekly show that features newsmaker interviews and panel discussions with other Journal staffers. Interview topics include guests' writings and current events. Panel discussions with the publication's writers and editors revolve around political, economic and cultural issues that people are talking about that week. Each half-hour episode ends with panelists discussing the best and worst stories in the news the previous week.
